<eesti>Avalikud tollilaod, tolliterminalid, vabatsoonid ja vabalaod sadamates </eesti>
<inglise>Public customs warehouses, customs terminals, free zones and free warehouses in ports </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Avalikud tollilaod, tolliterminalid ja vabatsoonid luuakse ning vabalaod asutatakse sadamates kaubanduse edendamiseks tolliseadustikuga kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Public customs warehouses, customs terminals, free zones and free warehouses are established in ports for the promotion of commerce pursuant to the procedure established by the Customs Code. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Taotluse sadamaalal vabatsooni loomiseks v&otilde;i vabalao asutamiseks esitab sadama valdaja teede- ja sideministrile. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A port authority shall submit an application for the establishment of a free zone or a free warehouse within the port area to the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Avalike tolliladude, tolliterminalide ja vabatsoonide loomise ning vabaladude asutamisega ei tohi kaasneda sadamateenuste osutamise vabaduse piiramine ning ebaausat konkurentsi p&otilde;hjustavate tingimuste loomine. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The establishment of public customs warehouses, customs terminals, free zones and free warehouses shall not result in limitation of the freedom to provide port services or the creation of conditions causing unfair competition. </inglise>
